Package: LWFBrook90R
Title: Run the LWF-Brook90 Hydrological Model From Within R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
person("Paul", "Schmidt-Walter", , "paul.schmidt-walter@nw-fva.de", role = c("aut", "cre")),
        person("Volodymyr", "Trotsiuk", , "vtrotsiuk@gmail.com", role = c("aut")),
        person("Klaus", "Hammel", , role = c("aut")),
        person("Martin", "Kennel", , role = c("aut")),
        person("Anthony", "Federer", ,"tony@ecoshift.net", role = c("aut"))
Description: Run the LWF-BROOK90 hydrological model within R. The central
    function creates the input objects from model control options, parameters, soil and
    climate data, runs the LWF-Brook90 hydrological model and returns the output files. 
    Additionally, submodels for defining vegetation dynamics and pedotransfer functions 
    for deriving soil hydraulic parameters are provided.
Depends: R (>= 3.1.0)
Imports:
    data.table (>= 1.10.4),
    vegperiod (>= 0.2.1),
    foreach,
    doSNOW,
	  snow,
	  sirad
